# Post-Coding Checks (Mandatory)

Run these after any code change.

## 1) Code Quality / Structure
- Verify no changed source file exceeds 500 lines.
- Keep all new files at <= 400 lines when possible.
- Confirm module boundaries remain clear.
- Confirm no secrets were added to source or docs.

## 2) Validation Commands
1. `[AI_CONTEXT_COMMAND]`
2. `[STRUCTURE_GUARD_COMMAND]`
3. `[LINT_COMMAND]`
4. `[FORMAT_CHECK_COMMAND]`
5. `[TYPECHECK_COMMAND]`
6. `[SMOKE_COMMAND]`
7. `[TARGETED_TEST_COMMAND]`
8. `[VERIFY_COMMAND]`

## 3) Documentation Sync
If paths, behavior, tests, or commands changed, update:
- `CHANGELOG.md`
- `AI_CONTEXT.md`
- `docs/INSTRUCTIONS_INDEX.md`
- `docs/WORKFLOW_COMMANDS.md`
- `docs/WORKFLOW_TEST_MATRIX.md`
- `docs/architecture/repository-map.md`

## 4) Security Regression Scan
- Confirm auth controls remain enforced.
- Confirm no unintended public write endpoints were introduced.
- Confirm secrets are not hardcoded.
